INSERT INTO knowledge_articles (title, content, embedded) VALUES
('How to Reset Your Password', 'If you cannot sign in or authenticate into your access account, you can initiate a password reset from the login screen. Click the forgot password link to receive a secure email with instructions. You must update your credentials within thirty minutes to avoid link expiration. If you are on the Enterprise Plan, password resets may be subject to your organization''s Single Sign-On configuration. Contact an Administrator or submit a Support Ticket if you do not receive the email.', false),
('Setting Up Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA)', 'Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA) adds an extra layer of security when you sign in to your access account. You can enable this feature within your Profile Management page by scanning a QR code with an authenticator app. If you lose access to your device, you must use a generated backup code to authenticate. Administrators on the Enterprise Plan can enforce 2FA for all members within their Organization Settings. Submit a support request if you are locked out and cannot bypass the 2FA prompt.', false),
('Configuring Single Sign-On (SSO)', 'Single Sign-On (SSO) allows users to authenticate using their corporate identity provider instead of standard login credentials. This feature is available exclusively on the Enterprise Plan and must be configured by an Administrator in the Organization Settings. We support SAML 2.0 and OpenID Connect protocols for seamless integration. Once enabled, users will be redirected to your provider''s portal before accessing the application. Please open a Support Ticket with your metadata file if you need assistance mapping attributes.', false),
('Resolving an Account Lockout', 'For security reasons, your access account will automatically trigger an account lockout after five failed authentication attempts. You must wait fifteen minutes before trying to sign in again, or an Administrator can manually unlock your profile from the Organization Settings. If you frequently experience lockouts, ensure your password manager is not submitting outdated credentials. Users on the Enterprise Plan utilizing Single Sign-On (SSO) should contact their internal IT department if lockouts persist. Submit a support request if you suspect a compromised account is causing the lockout.', false),
('Managing User Profile Management', 'Profile Management allows you to update your personal information, timezone, and communication preferences. Navigate to your avatar in the top right corner and select Profile to modify your details. Updating your email address will require you to re-authenticate to verify the new address. Administrators cannot edit personal profiles on behalf of users, but they can remove users from the organization. Always ensure your contact information is current to avoid email delivery issues and notification delays.', false),
('Downloading Invoices and Receipts', 'You can download all official invoices and receipts directly from the Billing Dashboard. Statements are generated automatically at the end of every billing cycle and include a detailed breakdown of your Subscription Billing. If you need to update your billing contact or tax information, modify these fields in your Organization Settings before the next renewal date. Each invoice contains a unique Invoice Number and Order ID for tracking purposes. Contact our billing team by opening a Support Ticket if a past statement is missing from your account history.', false),
('Handling Payment Failures', 'Payment failures usually occur when a credit card expires, lacks sufficient funds, or is blocked by your bank. When a transaction fails, our system immediately sends a notification delivery to your billing contact. You can update your payment method directly in the Billing Dashboard to authorize a new charge. If the payment is not resolved within three days, your subscription may be temporarily suspended. To avoid duplicate charges, ensure you only submit the updated payment information once.', false),
('Resolving Duplicate Charges', 'If you notice duplicate charges for the same Order ID on your credit card statement, please verify that a colleague did not accidentally process a parallel payment. Sometimes, refreshing the Billing Dashboard during a transaction can cause a visual duplication without an actual financial charge. If you confirm a genuine duplicate payment, please open a Support Ticket and include the Invoice Number and transaction dates. Our billing department will investigate the error and issue a billing adjustment or payment reversal. Refunds are typically processed back to the original payment method within five business days.', false),
('Understanding Refund Policy and Payment Reversals', 'If you require a refund or payment reversal, you must submit a Support Ticket within thirty days of the original charge. Our billing team will review the Invoice Number and Order ID to verify the eligibility for a billing adjustment. Refunds are typically processed back to the original payment method within five to seven business days. You can track the status of your case through the Billing Dashboard. Please ensure you provide a valid reason for the reversal to avoid processing delays.', false),
('Subscription Billing and Proration', 'Subscription Billing is processed automatically on the first day of your billing cycle. If you upgrade or downgrade your plan mid-cycle, the system will automatically calculate a prorated charge or credit for the remaining days. You can view these prorated adjustments on your next monthly invoice in the Billing Dashboard. Ensure your tax information is updated in Organization Settings so the prorated amount is calculated accurately. If you believe the proration is incorrect, open a Support Ticket with your Invoice Number for review.', false),
('Updating Tax Information', 'Accurate tax information ensures that your invoices reflect the correct local and regional tax rates. An Administrator can update your company name, address, and tax identification number in the Organization Settings menu. Once updated, all future invoices generated in the Billing Dashboard will apply the new tax calculations. We do not retroactively adjust taxes for past billing cycles unless a payment failure resulted in an unprocessed invoice. For specific tax compliance questions, please open a Support Ticket.', false),
('Upgrading to the Enterprise Plan', 'Upgrading to the Enterprise Plan unlocks advanced security features, custom integrations, and dedicated support hours. An Administrator can initiate the upgrade process from the Billing Dashboard by selecting the desired plan. The system will immediately apply a prorated charge to your current payment method based on the remaining days in your billing cycle. Once upgraded, you can configure Single Sign-On (SSO) and enforce Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA) across your organization. If you encounter payment failures during the upgrade, please submit a Support Ticket.', false),
('Downgrading to the Standard Plan', 'When you downgrade from the Enterprise Plan to the Standard Plan, the changes will take effect at the start of your next billing cycle. You will retain access to premium features like SSO and advanced API Versioning until the current cycle ends. An Administrator can schedule a downgrade in the Billing Dashboard at any time. Please ensure you export any advanced reports and verify your API Keys align with the Standard Plan limits before the transition. Open a Support Ticket if you need assistance evaluating your current usage.', false),
('Activating a Free Trial', 'New users can activate a Free Trial to explore the platform features for fourteen days without entering payment information. During the trial, you have limited access to the Developer Portal and standard support hours. To continue using the service after the trial expires, an Administrator must upgrade to the Standard Plan or Enterprise Plan via the Billing Dashboard. You will receive an email delivery notification five days before the trial ends. If the trial expires accidentally, open a Support Ticket to request a one-time extension.', false),
('Subscription Cancellation Process', 'To cancel your subscription, an Administrator must navigate to the Billing Dashboard and select the option to cancel the plan. The cancellation will take effect at the end of your current billing cycle, and you will not be charged for the next renewal. You will retain access to your data and support cases until the official cancellation date. Please ensure you perform a complete Data Export before the expiration date to avoid permanent data loss. If you cancel due to payment failures, please open a Support Ticket to see if a billing adjustment is possible.', false),
('Managing Subscription Renewals', 'Subscription renewals are processed automatically using the payment method stored in the Billing Dashboard. You will receive an email delivery notification seven days prior to your renewal date outlining the upcoming charge. If your payment method is expiring soon, please update it in Organization Settings to avoid payment failures. Renewals always generate a new Invoice Number and Order ID for your financial records. If a renewal fails, your account will enter a grace period before services are suspended.', false),
('Understanding Support Ticket Lifecycle', 'Every support request follows a structured ticket lifecycle from creation to resolution. When you submit a new case, it enters the open state and is automatically routed to an available Agent based on priority levels. You will receive a notification delivery via email whenever the status changes or an update is added to the case. If your issue is resolved, the case is marked as closed, but you can reopen it within fourteen days if the problem persists. Maintaining clear communication and providing an Order ID or Invoice Number helps expedite the support process.', false),
('Ticket Escalation Process', 'If a support request requires immediate attention beyond standard priority levels, it may qualify for ticket escalation. Users on the Enterprise Plan can request an escalation by replying to their existing case and stating the business impact. An Administrator can also flag critical issues by calling our dedicated support line during standard support hours. Once escalated, the case is assigned to a senior Agent who will provide updates every two hours until resolution. Please ensure you provide all relevant logs and an accurate Order ID to avoid delays during the escalation process.', false),
('Defining Priority Levels', 'Priority levels determine how quickly an Agent responds to your support ticket based on the severity of the issue. Standard priority includes minor bugs or general questions, while high priority covers system outages or payment failures affecting multiple users. When submitting a case, clearly state the business impact to ensure the system assigns the correct priority level. Misrepresenting priority to achieve faster response times may result in the case being downgraded by support staff. The Service Level Agreement (SLA) outlines exact response times for each tier.', false),
('Distinguishing Severity Levels', 'Severity levels are technically categorized by our engineering team to determine the root cause of an incident. While priority levels dictate response times, severity levels indicate the impact on the overall platform, such as a complete application crash or a minor UI glitch. A Severity 1 issue involves data loss or a compromised account and requires immediate ticket escalation. Users cannot manually set severity levels, but providing detailed troubleshooting steps in the support request helps engineers assess it accurately. Always include an Order ID if the issue involves billing discrepancies.', false),
('Support Hours and Coverage', 'Standard support hours are from 8 AM to 6 PM EST, Monday through Friday, for users on the Standard Plan. Enterprise Plan customers have access to 24/7 support for critical priority levels and security incident reporting. If you submit a support ticket outside of standard hours, it will be queued for review the next business day. You can view your current coverage tier in the Organization Settings menu. Please utilize the Knowledge Base for non-urgent troubleshooting outside of support hours.', false),
('Service Level Agreement (SLA) Guidelines', 'Our Service Level Agreement (SLA) defines the guaranteed response and resolution times based on your subscription plan and priority levels. For example, Enterprise Plan customers receive a one-hour response time for high priority support requests. If an SLA is breached due to a delayed notification delivery or other system issue, you can request a billing adjustment. The SLA does not cover issues arising from unsupported browsers or failing to meet system requirements. Please open a Support Ticket if you believe an SLA target has been missed.', false),
('Adding Attachments to a Support Request', 'When submitting a support ticket, adding attachments like screenshots and log files helps an Agent diagnose the issue faster. You can upload files directly in the case creation interface, provided they comply with our file upload limits. Ensure that attachments do not contain sensitive data, such as API Keys or full Invoice Numbers, to maintain security. If you experience a file upload failure, check your network connection or try compressing the file. All attachments are encrypted at rest within our secure support infrastructure.', false),
('Reopening a Closed Case', 'If a support request is marked as resolved but the problem persists, you have fourteen days to reopen the closed case. Navigate to your support history, locate the specific case, and click the reopen button to submit additional comments. Providing new troubleshooting steps or error messages helps an Agent quickly resume the investigation. If the fourteen-day window has expired, you must open a new Support Ticket and reference the previous case number. Reopening a case does not alter the original priority levels or SLA metrics.', false),
('API Authentication Overview', 'All API requests require proper API Authentication using a valid Bearer token. You can generate and manage your credentials in the Developer Portal under API Keys. Ensure you never expose your secret key in client-side code or public repositories to prevent a compromised account. If a key is accidentally leaked, an Administrator must immediately perform an API Key Rotation. Requests with missing or invalid authentication headers will receive an HTTP 401 Unauthorized status code.', false),
('Generating API Keys in the Developer Portal', 'The Developer Portal allows an Administrator to create new API Keys for programmatic access to the platform. Navigate to the API settings section and click generate key, ensuring you copy the secret value immediately as it cannot be retrieved later. Assign specific permissions to each key to enforce the principle of least privilege within your application. If you experience notification delays when using the API to create resources, verify your webhook configuration. Remember that exceeding your plan''s rate limit will result in an HTTP 429 error.', false),
('Implementing OAuth 2.0', 'Developers can implement OAuth 2.0 to allow third-party applications to authenticate without sharing raw credentials. This is the recommended approach for Single Sign-On (SSO) integrations and accessing user data securely. You must register your application in the Developer Portal to obtain a client ID and client secret. During the authentication flow, ensure your callback URL strictly matches the entry in your app configuration to prevent errors. If the token exchange fails, verify the granted permissions and check the HTTP Status Codes returned.', false),
('Handling HTTP 429 Rate Limiting', 'Our API enforces strict rate limiting to prevent abuse and ensure system stability for all clients. If you exceed your designated request quota, the API will return an HTTP 429 Too Many Requests status code. The response headers will include a retry-after duration, indicating when your client can safely resume sending requests. Developers should implement exponential backoff and retry logic to handle rate limiting errors gracefully. Upgrading to the Enterprise Plan may increase your throughput limits and reduce API latency.', false),
('Understanding HTTP Status Codes', 'Our API returns standard HTTP Status Codes to indicate the success or failure of a request. A 200-level code signifies success, while 400-level codes usually indicate an issue with your API Authentication or request payload. If you receive a 500-level error, it indicates a server-side problem, and you should open a Support Ticket immediately. Always inspect the JSON response body, as it provides specific error details beyond the standard HTTP code. Developers should build robust error handling to manage these codes effectively.', false),
('Implementing Pagination', 'Endpoints that return large datasets, such as retrieving Order IDs or Invoice Numbers, utilize pagination to maintain performance. Clients must send the page and size parameters to control the volume of data returned in a single response. The API response will include metadata indicating the total number of pages and the current page index. Failing to implement pagination correctly can lead to slow performance or an HTTP 429 rate limiting error. Always follow the pagination links provided in the response header to ensure data consistency.', false),
('Webhook Configuration Guide', 'Webhooks allow your application to receive real-time notification delivery when specific events occur, such as a subscription renewal or a support ticket update. An Administrator can register a webhook endpoint in the Developer Portal by providing a valid URL. Ensure your endpoint is secured using HTTPS and can validate the webhook signature to prevent spoofing. If endpoints continuously fail, the system will temporarily disable the webhook to prevent queue congestion. Test your configuration using the built-in send test event feature.', false),
('Webhook Retry Logic and Delays', 'If your webhook endpoint is unavailable or returns an error, our system will automatically attempt to resend the payload using exponential backoff. The initial retry occurs after one minute, with subsequent attempts increasing up to twenty-four hours. If all retries fail, you may experience notification delays for critical events like payment failures. You can monitor the delivery status and error logs directly in the Developer Portal. If a payload is lost due to a prolonged outage, you can manually request a replay by opening a Support Ticket.', false),
('Webhook Signature Validation', 'To ensure that a webhook payload was sent by our platform and not a malicious actor, your endpoint must perform signature validation. Each request includes a hash signature in the headers, generated using your secret API Keys. Your server should calculate the hash of the received payload and compare it to the signature header. If the signatures do not match, reject the request with an HTTP 403 Forbidden status code. Failing to validate signatures leaves your integration vulnerable to a compromised account scenario.', false),
('Using Idempotency Keys for API Calls', 'When performing sensitive operations like submitting a payment or creating an Order ID, you should include an idempotency key in your request header. This ensures that if a network timeout occurs and you retry the request, the system will not process it twice and cause duplicate charges. The idempotency key must be a unique string generated by your client for each specific transaction. If a retry is sent with the same key, the API will return the original successful response without re-executing the operation. This is a critical best practice for maintaining accurate subscription billing.', false),
('API Versioning and Deprecation Policy', 'We use API Versioning to introduce new features and breaking changes without disrupting existing integrations. The version is specified in the URL path, such as v1 or v2, and developers are encouraged to always reference the version explicitly. When a new version is released, the previous version enters a deprecation phase and is supported for twelve months. You can monitor deprecation timelines in the Developer Portal. To ensure a smooth transition, update your API Authentication logic and test all webhook configuration payloads against the new version before the cutoff date.', false),
('Inviting Users via Organization Settings', 'An Administrator can invite new members to the platform by navigating to the Organization Settings menu. Enter the email address of the invitee and assign appropriate roles such as Viewer or Agent before sending the invitation. The system will send an email delivery containing a secure link to authenticate and access the account. If the invitation expires, you can resend it from the user management dashboard. Ensure the invited user checks their spam folder if they experience notification delays.', false),
('Removing Users from an Organization', 'When an employee leaves your company, an Administrator must promptly remove their access account to prevent a compromised account scenario. Navigate to the user list in Organization Settings, select the inactive user, and click remove. The user will immediately lose the ability to sign in and view any shared support ticket history. Their personal API Keys will also be revoked instantly. If you need to transfer ownership of specific cases before removal, please ensure you update the assignee field first.', false),
('Assigning Roles: Administrator, Agent, and Viewer', 'Role-based access control ensures that users only have permissions relevant to their job functions. An Administrator has full control over Organization Settings, Billing Dashboard, and user management. An Agent can respond to support requests and manage priority levels, but cannot alter billing information. A Viewer has read-only access to reports and the Knowledge Base. Properly assigning roles minimizes security risks and prevents accidental configuration changes. If a user cannot access a feature, verify their assigned role in the user management portal.', false),
('Managing Granular Permissions', 'In addition to standard roles, Enterprise Plan customers can define granular permissions for specialized workflows. An Administrator can create custom roles in the Organization Settings to restrict access to specific API Keys or hide certain Invoice Numbers from standard users. This ensures compliance with internal security policies and data privacy regulations. When updating permissions, users may need to sign out and authenticate again for the changes to take effect. Open a Support Ticket if custom roles are not syncing properly across your organization.', false),
('Transferring Organization Ownership', 'If the primary Administrator leaves the company, you must transfer organization ownership to another active user. This process is initiated in the Organization Settings menu and requires the new owner to accept the responsibility via email delivery. The previous owner will immediately be downgraded to an Agent role upon successful transfer. Ensure the new owner has updated their Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA) settings before assuming control. If the current owner is unreachable, submit a Support Ticket with proof of corporate authority to request a manual override.', false),
('Enforcing Password Policy', 'A strong password policy is the first line of defense against unauthorized access and a compromised account. Administrators on the Enterprise Plan can enforce minimum length, special characters, and mandatory rotation intervals in the Organization Settings. If a user attempts to sign in with a non-compliant password, the system will force a reset before granting access. Regularly updating credentials mitigates the risk of suspicious login activity. Users who frequently forget their password should enable Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA) for added security.', false),
('Recovering a Compromised Account', 'If you suspect your access account has been compromised, immediately attempt a password reset and contact an Administrator. The Administrator must revoke all active sessions and perform an API Key Rotation to prevent unauthorized data extraction. You should also review the Billing Dashboard for any unauthorized duplicate charges or changes to your subscription billing. Open a Support Ticket with high priority levels to report the security incident reporting. Our security team will investigate the suspicious login logs and assist with securing your profile management data.', false),
('Investigating Suspicious Login Activity', 'Our security system monitors for suspicious login attempts to protect against a compromised account. If we detect an authentication request from an unrecognized device or location, we will temporarily restrict access. You will receive an immediate notification delivery prompting you to verify the sign in attempt. If you do not recognize the activity, change your password immediately and enable Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA). Report any persistent unauthorized access as a security incident to our support team.', false),
('API Key Rotation Best Practices', 'Regularly performing an API Key Rotation is a critical security best practice to prevent credential leakage. Administrators should generate a new key in the Developer Portal and update their application configuration before deactivating the old key. This dual-key approach ensures a seamless transition without causing API Authentication failures or notification delays. Once the new key is active, immediately revoke the old key to invalidate any compromised credentials. Enterprise Plan users can automate this process using secure vault integrations.', false),
('Security Incident Reporting Procedures', 'If you identify a vulnerability or experience a data breach, immediately initiate our security incident reporting procedures. Do not discuss the issue in a public Support Ticket, instead, contact our dedicated security team via the encrypted portal in the Developer Portal. Provide all relevant details, including the timestamp, affected Order IDs, and any suspicious login IP addresses. Our engineering team will prioritize the issue with the highest severity levels and provide updates through a secure communication channel. Customers who report valid vulnerabilities may be eligible for a billing adjustment.', false),
('GDPR Compliance and Data Privacy', 'Our platform is fully compliant with GDPR regulations to ensure strict data privacy for all users. We provide tools that allow an Administrator to manage consent and control how personal data is processed within the Organization Settings. You can review our specific data retention policy to understand how long different types of information are stored. If you receive a request from a user to exercise their data rights, you must process it within thirty days. For legal inquiries regarding compliance, please open a Support Ticket with legal documentation attached.', false),
('Requesting Account Deletion', 'To comply with GDPR and data privacy regulations, you can request permanent account deletion at any time. Submit a Support Ticket specifying your intent, and our security team will verify your identity to prevent unauthorized removal. Once processed, all associated data, including billing history and support cases, is purged according to our retention policy. This action is irreversible and will immediately terminate your ability to sign in. Please perform a full Data Export before requesting deletion if you need to retain records.', false),
('Performing a Data Export', 'An Administrator can perform a comprehensive Data Export from the Organization Settings menu to retrieve all account information. This includes user profiles, support ticket histories, API Keys metadata, and complete Billing Dashboard records. The system generates a secure download link sent via email delivery once the archive is ready. Due to file upload limits on our processing servers, very large exports may be split into multiple zip files. If the download link expires, you can request a new one by reopening the generated support case.', false),
('Data Retention Policy Guidelines', 'Our data retention policy dictates how long we store user information after an account is deactivated. Standard data is retained for ninety days to allow for billing adjustment processing and dispute resolution. After this period, all personally identifiable information is permanently purged from our active databases and backups. Enterprise Plan customers can request customized retention timelines to meet specific regulatory compliance requirements. To view the specific timeline for your data, consult the compliance documentation in the Knowledge Base.', false),
('Configuring Privacy Settings', 'Users can manage their individual privacy settings from the Profile Management page. This includes opting out of marketing communications and controlling visibility within the organization''s directory. An Administrator can also configure global privacy controls in the Organization Settings to restrict third-party analytics tracking. Modifying these settings does not affect essential email delivery for Support Ticket updates or critical system alerts. If you believe your preferences are not being honored, please open a Support Ticket for investigation.', false),
('Supported Browsers and System Requirements', 'For optimal performance, ensure your system meets the minimum system requirements before accessing the platform. We officially support the latest versions of Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Microsoft Edge, and Safari. Using unsupported browsers may result in slow performance, rendering glitches, or an inability to authenticate properly. We recommend keeping your browser updated to the latest stable version to ensure compatibility with advanced security features like Single Sign-On (SSO). Clearing your browser cache periodically can also resolve unexpected display issues.', false),
('Mobile Support and Application Access', 'While we do not offer a dedicated native mobile application, our platform is fully responsive and supports mobile access via standard web browsers. Users can easily view their support ticket history, update profile management details, and check Billing Dashboard summaries from their smartphones. Certain complex administrative tasks, such as configuring API Keys or webhook endpoints, are best performed on a desktop interface. If you experience UI misalignment on a specific device, please submit a Support Ticket with a screenshot. Always ensure your mobile browser is updated to meet system requirements.', false),
('File Upload Limits and Restrictions', 'When adding attachments to a support ticket or uploading data via the Developer Portal, you must adhere to our file upload limits. The maximum file size per upload is twenty-five megabytes, and we only accept standard formats such as PDF, PNG, JPEG, and CSV. If you need to share larger datasets for troubleshooting purposes, please use an external secure link and share it in your case. Attempting to upload executable files will result in an immediate file upload failure for security reasons. Compressing files into a zip archive can help bypass individual format restrictions.', false),
('Notification Delivery and Routing', 'The notification delivery system ensures you receive timely updates regarding your account, billing, and support requests. An Administrator can customize routing rules in the Organization Settings to send specific alerts to different team members. For example, payment failure alerts can be routed directly to your billing contact, while API rate limiting warnings can be sent to developers. If you experience notification delays, verify that your email server is not blocking our domain. You can also view a comprehensive log of all sent notifications in the audit trail.', false),
('Troubleshooting Slow Performance', 'If you experience slow performance while navigating the platform, first verify your internet connection and system requirements. Clearing your browser cache often resolves rendering issues and improves load times when accessing the Billing Dashboard. Close unnecessary background tabs or applications that might be consuming bandwidth and causing notification delays. If the application remains sluggish, submit a Support Ticket with details about your supported browsers and the specific pages affected. Our engineering team monitors system health to prevent widespread degradation and application crash scenarios.', false),
('Resolving Application Crash Issues', 'An unexpected application crash can usually be resolved by refreshing your browser or restarting your session. Before reporting the issue, verify that you are using one of our officially supported browsers and that it is fully updated. If the crash occurs while performing a specific action, such as generating an Invoice Number, document the exact steps taken to reproduce the error. Submit a Support Ticket with any console error logs or screenshots to help our engineering team identify the root cause. Frequent crashes may indicate an issue with your local browser cache or a conflicting extension.', false),
('Clearing Browser Cache for Login Problems', 'If you are experiencing login problems such as blank screens or immediate sign out errors, your browser cache may contain corrupted session data. Clearing your cache and cookies forces the browser to fetch the latest authentication tokens from our servers. After clearing the cache, close all browser windows, reopen them, and attempt to authenticate again. If you are utilizing Single Sign-On (SSO), ensure your corporate identity provider is not experiencing an outage. If the issue persists, try accessing the platform using an incognito window to rule out extension interference.', false),
('Resolving Email Delivery and Notification Delays', 'If you are not receiving password reset emails or Support Ticket updates, you may be experiencing notification delays. First, check your spam or junk folder to ensure our emails are not being incorrectly filtered. Ensure your IT department has whitelisted our domain to prevent strict firewalls from blocking essential email delivery. If emails are still missing, an Administrator can verify the correct address is listed in Profile Management. Open a support request if you suspect a global delivery failure on our end.', false),
('Handling File Upload Failure', 'If you encounter a file upload failure when adding attachments to a support case, first verify the file size does not exceed our file upload limits. Ensure the file format is explicitly supported and not blocked by our security scanners. Renaming the file extension or removing special characters from the filename often resolves invalid format errors. If the upload consistently fails across multiple browsers, try compressing the file into a zip archive. As a workaround, you can provide a secure external download link within the ticket description.', false),
('Managing 90-Day Password Expiration', 'To maintain strict security, your access account enforces a 90-day password expiration policy. You will receive an email alert five days before your credentials expire, prompting you to authenticate and update your profile. To change your password, navigate to Profile Management and submit a new secure string that complies with the password reuse policy. If you fail to update your credentials in time, the system will immediately sign you out. You will then need to initiate a standard password reset via the login screen to regain access.', false),
('Configuring 15-Minute Session Timeout', 'For your protection, the platform enforces a 15-minute session timeout period of inactivity. If you do not interact with the dashboard or make an API request within this timeframe, your access account will be automatically suspended. You will be prompted to sign in again to resume your workflow and restore your session token. Administrators on the Enterprise Plan cannot disable this security feature, but they can adjust the maximum duration to a shorter interval in Organization Settings. This standard safeguard helps prevent unauthorized access on unattended workstations.', false),
('Enabling Remember Me for Trusted Devices', 'When you authenticate on the login screen, you can check the Remember Me box to bypass the standard 15-minute session timeout on trusted devices. This feature installs a secure persistent token in your browser cache that keeps you signed in for up to thirty days. You must still complete Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA) if your organization requires it. For security reasons, do not enable this feature on public or shared computers to avoid a compromised account. You can revoke trusted devices at any time from the Security Settings menu.', false),
('Completing Email Verification Within 24 Hours', 'When you create a new access account or update your email in Profile Management, the system sends a verification link to your inbox. You must click this link within 24 hours to confirm ownership of the email address. If the link expires, you will need to request a new verification email from the login screen. Until the email is verified, certain features like API Key generation and Billing Dashboard access will remain restricted. If you do not receive the alert, check your spam folder or contact an Administrator.', false),
('Recovering Your Username', 'If you forget the username associated with your access account, you can use the automated recovery tool on the login screen. Click the Forgot Username link and enter the email address registered to your profile. The system will send an alert containing your exact username to that inbox. For security reasons, we cannot provide your username over a Support Ticket or via phone. If you no longer have access to the registered email, an Administrator must update your profile information.', false),
('Reviewing Login History', 'You can monitor your access account security by reviewing your login history in the Security Settings menu. This log displays the timestamp, IP address, and browser type for every successful authentication attempt over the past thirty days. If you notice a suspicious login from an unrecognized device or location, immediately change your password and enable Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA). Enterprise Plan customers can export this data to a security information and event management system. Report any unauthorized access immediately through our security incident reporting procedures.', false),
('Managing Trusted Devices', 'The platform maintains a list of trusted devices that bypass standard identity challenges after you successfully authenticate. You can view and manage this list within your Security Settings. If you lose a laptop or sell a phone, you should immediately revoke its trusted status to prevent unauthorized access. Revoking a device will force the next user to complete the full sign in process, including 2FA. This proactive device management ensures your workspace remains secure even if hardware is compromised.', false),
('Initiating Account Recovery Without 2FA', 'If you lose access to your Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA) device, you must use a saved backup code to sign in to your access account. These codes were generated when you initially configured 2FA in your Profile Management settings. If you did not save your backup codes, you must open a high priority Support Ticket to begin the manual account recovery process. An Administrator will need to verify your identity through alternative means before temporarily disabling 2FA. Support agents cannot bypass 2FA without administrative approval and proper identity verification.', false),
('Identifying and Reporting Phishing Attempts', 'Phishing attempts often involve fraudulent emails pretending to be from our support team, asking you to click a link and sign in to verify your access account. Remember that our team will never ask you to confirm your password or API Keys over email. If you receive a suspicious message, do not click any links and forward the email to our security team via the Developer Portal. You can also report the incident by opening a Support Ticket marked as a security incident reporting. Always verify the sender domain before entering your credentials on any login page.', false),
('Active Session Management', 'Administrators can view and terminate active user sessions directly from the Organization Settings dashboard. This feature is useful when an employee is terminated unexpectedly or a compromised account is detected. Terminating a session immediately signs the user out across all supported browsers and devices. The user will be forced to re-authenticate to regain access to the workspace. Regularly auditing active sessions is a recommended practice for maintaining strict security compliance.', false),
('Downloading Audit Logs', 'Enterprise Plan customers can download comprehensive audit logs directly from the Organization Settings menu. These logs record all administrative actions, user role changes, and modifications to API Keys for up to one year. The data is exported as a CSV file and securely delivered via email delivery within 24 hours. Reviewing these logs regularly helps identify unauthorized changes and maintain compliance with SOC2 and ISO27001 standards. Contact support if you need logs older than one year for legal discovery.', false),
('Configuring Security Notifications', 'You can customize your security alert preferences within your Profile Management page. By default, the system sends an immediate email delivery when a new device signs in or when an API Key is generated. You can opt to receive these alerts via SMS notifications if your organization has enabled this feature. Adjusting these settings ensures you are immediately aware of any potential unauthorized access. We strongly recommend leaving critical security alerts enabled to prevent a compromised account.', false),
('Enforcing IP Restrictions', 'Administrators on the Enterprise Plan can enhance security by implementing IP Restrictions within the Organization Settings. This feature ensures that users can only sign in from approved corporate networks or specific IP addresses. If a user attempts to authenticate from an unrecognized location, the system will deny access and trigger a security notification. To avoid locking out remote workers, ensure you add their static IPs to the whitelist before enabling this restriction. This feature is highly recommended for maintaining strict data privacy.', false),
('Enforcing Password Reuse Policy', 'To encourage strong credential hygiene, the platform enforces a strict password reuse policy. When you update your password in Profile Management, you cannot use any of your previous five credentials. This policy works in conjunction with the 90-day password expiration to mitigate the risk of a compromised account. If you struggle to think of new passwords, consider using a secure enterprise password manager. Users utilizing Single Sign-On (SSO) are exempt from this policy as authentication is handled externally.', false),
('Handling Failed Subscription Renewal', 'If your credit card is declined during a subscription renewal, our system will immediately send a payment failure alert to your billing contact. You will enter a three-day grace period during which your workspace remains fully active. To prevent account suspension, update your Payment Method in the Billing Dashboard before the grace period expires. If the payment continues to fail, your API Quotas will be reduced to zero and users will be unable to sign in. Open a Support Ticket if you believe your bank is blocking the transaction erroneously.', false),
('Verifying Refund Eligibility', 'Refunds and payment reversals are only eligible for charges incurred within the last thirty days. To request a billing adjustment, open a Support Ticket with the specific Invoice Number and Order ID. Our billing team will review your account history and the reason for the request. Please note that refunds cannot be issued for expired promotional credits or partial month usage on annual plans. Approved refunds are processed back to the original Payment Method within five business days.', false),
('Applying Coupon Codes in the Billing Dashboard', 'You can apply coupon codes during the checkout process when upgrading your subscription plan. Navigate to the Billing Dashboard, select your desired plan, and enter the promotional code in the designated field. The system will validate the code and display the adjusted proration before you authorize the charge. Coupon codes cannot be applied retroactively to past invoices or combined with other promotional offers. If your code is expired or invalid, the system will display an error message explaining the reason.', false),
('Tracking Promotional Credits', 'Promotional credits are applied to your account as a balance and are automatically deducted before charging your primary Payment Method. You can view your current credit balance and expiration dates in the Billing Dashboard. These credits typically expire ninety days after issuance and cannot be extended. Refunds cannot be issued for expired promotional credits under any circumstances. If you have a question about a specific credit allocation, please provide the relevant Order ID in a Support Ticket.', false),
('Supported Currencies for Billing', 'The platform currently supports billing in United States Dollars (USD), Euros (EUR), and British Pounds (GBP). You can select your preferred currency in the Organization Settings before your first subscription renewal. Once a currency is selected and an invoice is generated, it cannot be changed without canceling and re-subscribing. Currency conversion rates are updated daily based on current market rates. Ensure your tax information matches the selected currency region to avoid billing delays.', false),
('Updating Payment Methods', 'An Administrator can add or remove Payment Methods at any time within the Billing Dashboard. We accept all major credit cards, Automated Clearing House (ACH) transfers, and wire transfers for Enterprise Plan customers. When you add a new card, we perform a temporary authorization hold to verify the funds, which is released within 24 hours. To avoid payment failures, ensure your billing address and postal code match your bank records exactly. You can designate a default card for automatic subscription billing.', false),
('Designating a Billing Contact', 'While an Administrator manages the overall workspace, the billing contact is the specific individual who receives invoices and payment failure alerts. You can assign a billing contact in the Organization Settings menu by entering their email address. This user does not need full administrative rights but will receive all financial notifications. Keeping this contact updated ensures that critical billing alerts do not go unnoticed. If your billing contact leaves the company, update this field immediately to avoid service interruption.', false),
('Disabling Auto Billing', 'If you prefer to manually pay your invoices, an Administrator can disable auto billing in the Billing Dashboard. When auto billing is turned off, you will receive an email delivery with your Invoice Number at the start of your cycle. You will have fifteen days to submit a manual payment before your workspace is suspended. If you forget to pay, your API Quotas will be set to zero and users will be unable to authenticate. Re-enabling auto billing will immediately charge the default Payment Method for any outstanding balances.', false),
('Understanding Proration Examples', 'When you upgrade or downgrade your subscription mid-cycle, the system calculates a prorated charge or credit based on the remaining days. For example, if you upgrade from the Standard Plan to the Enterprise Plan halfway through the month, you will be charged fifty percent of the price difference on your next invoice. This proration appears as a separate line item on your Billing Dashboard. If you downgrade, the remaining credit is applied to your next renewal and is not eligible for a refund. Always review the proration breakdown before confirming a plan change.', false),
('Comparing Standard and Enterprise Plans', 'The Standard Plan is designed for small teams and includes basic support hours and limited API Quotas. The Enterprise Plan unlocks advanced security features like Single Sign-On (SSO), IP Restrictions, and 24/7 priority support. Enterprise customers also receive expanded workspace limits and dedicated storage quotas. You can view a detailed plan comparison matrix in the Organization Settings menu. Consider scheduling a consultation with our sales team to determine which tier best fits your usage requirements.', false),
('Checking Feature Availability', 'Feature availability is strictly tied to your current subscription plan and any active feature flags. If you attempt to use a feature restricted to the Enterprise Plan, the system will display an upgrade prompt. Administrators can view which features are currently enabled for their workspace in the Organization Settings. Some beta features may be enabled manually by support staff upon request. If you believe a feature is missing erroneously, open a Support Ticket for investigation.', false),
('Navigating Workspace Limits', 'A workspace represents your isolated environment within the platform, and its limits are determined by your subscription plan. The Standard Plan allows for one workspace, while the Enterprise Plan supports up to ten distinct workspaces. If you reach your workspace limit, you must upgrade your plan or delete an existing workspace. Deleting a workspace permanently removes all associated data, support tickets, and API Keys. Ensure you perform a complete Data Export before deleting a workspace to avoid data loss.', false),
('Monitoring Storage Limits', 'File uploads, attachments, and generated reports all count toward your organizational storage limit. The Standard Plan includes fifty gigabytes of storage, while the Enterprise Plan provides one terabyte. You can monitor your current storage usage via the visual indicator in the Billing Dashboard. If you exceed your limit, you will be unable to add new attachments to support requests until space is freed up. Contact sales to purchase additional storage blocks if your usage consistently exceeds the standard allocation.', false),
('Managing User Limits', 'Your subscription plan dictates the maximum number of active users allowed in your organization. Standard Plan customers are capped at fifty users, while Enterprise Plan customers have unlimited seats subject to a fair use policy. If you attempt to invite a new user beyond your limit, the system will block the action and prompt you to upgrade. Deactivating a former employee frees up a seat immediately without requiring a plan change. You can monitor your current user count in the Organization Settings menu.', false),
('Reviewing API Quotas and Rate Limits', 'To ensure platform stability, all API requests are subject to rate limiting based on your subscription plan. The Standard Plan allows one hundred requests per minute, while the Enterprise Plan permits one thousand requests per minute. If you exceed this quota, the API will return an HTTP 429 Too Many Requests status code. Developers must implement an exponential backoff retry strategy to handle these temporary blocks gracefully. You can monitor your real-time API usage and quota limits in the Developer Portal.', false),
('Exploring Enterprise Features', 'The Enterprise Plan is tailored for large organizations requiring strict governance and security. Key features include detailed audit logs, granular permissions, and custom integration support. Enterprise customers also benefit from a dedicated Account Manager and prioritized ticket escalation during high traffic periods. Single Sign-On (SSO) and enforced Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA) are standard security inclusions. Contact our sales team through the Developer Portal to discuss custom API quotas and uptime SLAs.', false),
('Using OAuth Refresh Tokens', 'When implementing OAuth 2.0, the platform issues an access token valid for sixty minutes and a refresh token valid for twenty-four hours. Before the access token expires, your client application must use the refresh token to obtain a new access token without requiring the user to sign in again. If the refresh token expires, the user must re-authenticate through the standard web flow. Ensure your application securely stores these tokens to prevent a compromised account. Review the API Documentation for specific endpoint details regarding token renewal.', false),
('Handling Access Token Expiration', 'Access tokens issued by our OAuth 2.0 provider are strictly valid for sixty minutes after generation. Once the token expires, any API request using it will fail with an HTTP 401 Unauthorized status code. Your application must gracefully catch this error and trigger the refresh token flow. Do not attempt to authenticate on every request, as this will quickly exhaust your rate limits. Properly managing token expiration ensures smooth API performance and reduces notification delays.', false),
('Preparing for API Version Deprecation', 'When a new major API version is released, the previous version enters a deprecation phase lasting exactly twelve months. During this period, the older version remains fully functional but receives no new feature updates. Developers are notified via email delivery and dashboard alerts about the upcoming sunset date. After the twelve-month period, requests to the deprecated version will return an HTTP 410 Gone error. You must update your API Authentication logic and test all integrations in the Developer Portal before the cutoff.', false),
('Following API Best Practices', 'When integrating with our platform, always use the official SDKs available in the Developer Portal to ensure compatibility. Implement proper error handling for all HTTP Status Codes, specifically managing HTTP 429 rate limits with exponential backoff. Use idempotency keys for all POST and PUT requests to prevent duplicate charges and data corruption. Never hardcode API Keys into your source code; instead, use environment variables and secure vaults. Following these guidelines ensures your integration remains stable during high traffic periods.', false),
('Official SDK Support', 'We provide officially supported Software Development Kits (SDKs) for Java, Python, and Node.js to simplify API Authentication and request formatting. These SDKs automatically handle pagination, retry strategies, and parameter serialization. You can download the latest versions and view comprehensive code examples in the Developer Portal. Using outdated SDK versions may result in unexpected timeout handling or deprecated endpoint calls. Open a Support Ticket if you encounter bugs or require assistance with SDK implementation.', false),
('Handling Request Validation Errors', 'If you submit an API request with malformed JSON or missing required fields, the system will return an HTTP 400 Bad Request status code. The response body will contain a detailed JSON object identifying the exact validation errors for each parameter. Carefully review the API Documentation to ensure your payload matches the expected schema and data types. Implementing client-side validation before sending the request can significantly reduce these errors. Do not retry the exact same request if it fails validation, as it will continue to fail.', false),
('Implementing a Retry Strategy for HTTP 429', 'When your application receives an HTTP 429 status code, it must immediately cease sending requests and evaluate the retry-after header. The recommended strategy is exponential backoff, where you wait one second, then two, then four, up to a maximum of five retry attempts. Failing to implement this strategy can result in your API Keys being temporarily suspended for aggressive polling. Ensure your retry logic also accounts for idempotency to prevent duplicate operations upon successful retry. Proper timeout handling ensures system stability for all users.', false),
('Managing API Timeout Handling', 'Our API enforces a strict thirty-second timeout for all synchronous endpoints. If your client application takes longer to process a response, the connection will be terminated and you will receive a timeout error. For long-running operations such as bulk data imports, utilize the asynchronous job endpoints which return a job ID for status polling. Ensure your HTTP client is configured with a timeout limit slightly below thirty seconds to catch network hangs gracefully. Implementing proper timeout handling prevents thread blocking and application crashes.', false),
('Idempotency Examples for Payment Processing', 'When submitting a payment or creating an Order ID via the API, always include an idempotency key in your request header to prevent duplicate charges. If a network timeout occurs and you retry the request within the 24-hour window, the system recognizes the unique key and returns the original successful response. For example, if you submit a charge with a specific key and receive an HTTP 429 error, retrying with the same key ensures the customer is only billed once. This strategy is crucial for maintaining accurate subscription billing and avoiding manual payment reversals. Developers can find specific code examples in the API Documentation.', false),
('Recovering Deleted API Keys', 'When you generate new API Keys in the Developer Portal, the secret value is displayed exactly once for security purposes. API Keys cannot be recovered after deletion or if you lose the copied value from your secure vault. If you misplace your credentials, you must immediately perform an API Key Rotation by creating a new key and deleting the old one. Support agents cannot retrieve or decrypt deleted keys on your behalf. Always store your keys in a secure password manager to prevent a compromised account scenario.', false),
('Listing Webhook Event Types', 'Our platform emits various webhook event types including ticket.created, billing.refunded, and user.deactivated. Each event type delivers a specific JSON payload structure that your application must parse and handle accordingly. You can view the complete list of available event types and their schemas in the Developer Portal. When configuring your webhook endpoint, you can choose to subscribe to all events or filter for specific triggers. Properly filtering events reduces unnecessary server load and prevents notification delays.', false),
('Reviewing Webhook Delivery Logs', 'The Developer Portal maintains a comprehensive log of all webhook delivery attempts for the past thirty days. For each event, you can view the exact request payload, the HTTP response code from your server, and the response body. If your endpoint returns a non-2xx status code, the log will indicate that the delivery failed. Reviewing these logs is essential for debugging failed integrations and ensuring your automation flows are executing correctly. You can also manually replay specific events from the log interface if needed.', false),
('Handling Failed Webhook Deliveries', 'If your webhook endpoint is unavailable or returns an error, our system will automatically attempt to resend the payload. The initial retry occurs after one minute, with subsequent attempts following an exponential backoff schedule up to twenty-four hours. The system will perform a maximum of five retry attempts before permanently marking the delivery as failed. If all attempts fail, you may experience notification delays for critical events like payment failures. You can manually request a replay of failed events from the delivery logs in the Developer Portal.', false),
('Performing Webhook Secret Rotation', 'To maintain strict security, it is best practice to perform webhook secret rotation periodically. In the Developer Portal, you can generate a new signing secret while keeping the old one temporarily active. Update your endpoint validation logic to accept signatures from the new secret, then deactivate the old secret once confirmed. This dual-secret approach ensures a seamless transition without causing failed deliveries. Never expose your webhook secret in client-side code or public repositories.', false),
('Webhook HTTPS Requirements', 'All webhook endpoints must be secured using a valid HTTPS certificate to ensure data privacy in transit. The platform will refuse to send payloads to URLs using unencrypted HTTP connections. Your server must support TLS 1.2 or higher and possess a certificate issued by a recognized certificate authority. Self-signed certificates are not supported and will result in failed deliveries. Ensure your firewall allows inbound traffic from our designated IP ranges to prevent connection timeouts.', false),
('Webhook IP Whitelisting', 'To enhance security, you can configure your firewall to only accept webhook requests from our designated IP addresses. The current list of valid IP ranges is available in the Developer Portal under webhook configuration. This prevents malicious actors from spoofing webhook payloads to your endpoints. We recommend subscribing to our IP change notifications via email to ensure your whitelist remains up to date. If your server is behind a load balancer, ensure it correctly forwards the client IP for signature validation.', false),
('Structuring Department Management', 'Enterprise Plan customers can organize their workspace into distinct departments for better user and ticket management. An Administrator can create departments in the Organization Settings and assign a Department Head to manage local users. This structure allows for localized reporting and ensures that support tickets are routed to the correct internal teams. Departments do not affect Billing Dashboard access but are crucial for granular permissions. You can easily reassign users between departments as your organization evolves.', false),
('Creating Internal Teams', 'Within your organization, you can create internal teams to group agents by expertise or product line. Teams are utilized in ticket assignment rules to automatically route support requests to the appropriate personnel. An Administrator can configure team hierarchies and designate team leaders in the Organization Settings. This structure is essential for maintaining SLA compliance and ensuring efficient case resolution. Teams can also be used to filter the Knowledge Base and restrict article visibility.', false),
('Transferring Workspace Ownership', 'If the primary workspace owner leaves the company, an Administrator must initiate an ownership transfer. The current owner must navigate to Organization Settings, select a new administrator, and authorize the transfer via email. The new owner will immediately inherit full control over the Billing Dashboard, API Keys, and user management. If the current owner is completely unreachable, you must open a high priority Support Ticket with legal proof of corporate authority. Ensure the new owner has Multi-Factor Authentication (2FA) enabled before assuming control.', false),
('Restoring Deleted Organizations', 'When an organization is deleted, it enters a soft-deleted state for exactly ninety days before permanent purging. During this retention period, a workspace owner can request restoration by opening a high priority Support Ticket. You must provide the original Order ID and verify administrative authority to proceed. Deleted organizations cannot be restored after the retention period expires under any circumstances. Always perform a complete Data Export before requesting deletion to prevent irreversible data loss.', false),
('Performing User Deactivation', 'When an employee leaves the company, an Administrator should deactivate their access account rather than deleting it entirely. Deactivation immediately revokes the user''s ability to sign in and invalidates their active sessions and API Keys. However, it preserves the user''s historical data and past support ticket assignments for audit purposes. Deactivated users do not count toward your active user limits. If the employee returns, you can easily reactivate their profile to restore their previous access.', false),
('Executing Bulk User Import', 'Administrators can add multiple users simultaneously by utilizing the bulk user import feature in the Organization Settings. You must upload a specifically formatted CSV file containing the email addresses, names, and assigned roles for each new user. The system will validate the file and send an email verification link to each individual within 24 hours. Ensure your CSV strictly follows the provided template to avoid request validation errors. Users will not be able to authenticate until they complete the verification process.', false),
('Adding Internal Notes to Tickets', 'Agents can add internal notes to a support ticket to document troubleshooting steps or communicate with other team members. These notes are completely invisible to the customer and do not trigger an email delivery alert. Internal notes are essential for maintaining context during ticket escalation or when transferring a case between departments. Ensure you do not accidentally paste sensitive information like API Keys or passwords into these notes. All internal notes are retained permanently in the audit logs for compliance purposes.', false),
('Merging Duplicate Support Requests', 'If a customer opens multiple support tickets for the exact same issue, an Agent can merge them into a single primary case. Merging consolidates all communication, attachments, and internal notes into the primary ticket. The secondary ticket is automatically closed with a resolution code indicating it was merged. This process prevents duplicate work and ensures the SLA is tracked accurately on a single case. Be cautious when merging, as this action cannot be undone by support agents.', false),
('Splitting Complex Support Tickets', 'Sometimes a single support request contains multiple distinct issues that require different teams. In this scenario, an Agent can split the ticket to create a new, separate case. The original ticket retains the primary issue, while the newly created ticket receives the secondary problem. Both cases are linked together in the system for reference, but their priority levels and SLAs are tracked independently. Splitting ensures that complex issues are resolved faster by specialized departments.', false),
('Automating Ticket Assignment', 'Administrators can configure automatic ticket assignment rules within the Organization Settings to streamline support workflows. Rules can be based on keywords in the subject, specific customer domains, or the selected category. For example, any case containing the word refund can be automatically routed to the billing department. Properly configured assignment rules reduce response times and ensure cases reach the appropriately skilled Agent immediately. You can test these rules using the sandbox environment before applying them to live support requests.', false),
('Updating Ticket Statuses', 'Every support ticket follows a specific lifecycle marked by its current status. When a case is first opened, it is marked as Pending until an Agent responds. Once the Agent replies, the status changes to Waiting on Customer to indicate action is required from the user. When the user replies, it reverts to Pending. An Agent manually sets the status to Resolved when a solution is provided, and the case auto-closes after fourteen days if there is no further communication.', false),
('Applying Resolution Codes', 'When a support ticket is marked as Resolved, the Agent must apply a specific resolution code to categorize the outcome. Common codes include Issue Fixed, Duplicate Ticket, User Error, and Cannot Reproduce. These codes are essential for generating accurate reporting metrics in the Billing Dashboard and identifying systemic problems. Administrators can customize the available resolution codes in the Organization Settings. Applying the correct code ensures accurate customer satisfaction survey routing and SLA compliance tracking.', false),
('Completing Customer Satisfaction Surveys', 'When a support ticket is automatically closed after the fourteen-day window, the system sends a customer satisfaction survey to the user. The survey asks the customer to rate their experience with the Agent and the overall resolution process on a scale of one to five. This feedback is visible to the Agent and their direct manager in the internal dashboard. Consistently low scores may trigger a ticket escalation to a senior team member. We highly encourage users to complete these surveys to help us improve our support hours and service quality.', false),
('Understanding the Reopen Policy for Closed Cases', 'If a support request is marked as Resolved but the issue persists, you have exactly fourteen days to reopen the closed case. You can reopen a case by replying directly to the original email thread or logging into the portal and adding a new comment. If the fourteen-day reopen window has expired, the system will prompt you to open a new Support Ticket. You should reference the old case number in the new ticket description to ensure the Agent has full context. Reopening a case does not reset the original SLA or priority levels.', false),
('Configuring Email Preferences and Digest Notifications', 'Users can fine-tune their email preferences in the Profile Management section to control alert frequency. Instead of receiving an immediate alert for every support ticket update, you can opt to receive a daily digest notification. This digest compiles all non-urgent updates into a single email delivery sent at a designated time each morning. Critical security notifications and payment failure alerts will still be sent immediately regardless of this setting. Adjusting these preferences helps prevent notification fatigue during high traffic periods.', false),
('Optimizing Browser Performance for Large Dashboards', 'If you experience slow performance while loading large data tables in the Billing Dashboard, your browser cache may be struggling with memory allocation. Ensure you are using one of our officially supported browsers and that hardware acceleration is enabled in your settings. Closing unnecessary background tabs can free up RAM and significantly improve rendering times. For extremely large datasets, utilize the API to export the data instead of relying on visual pagination. Clearing your browser cache weekly is a recommended practice to prevent UI glitches.', false),
('Understanding SOC2 and ISO27001 Compliance', 'Our platform undergoes annual third-party audits to maintain strict SOC2 Type II and ISO27001 certifications. These certifications verify that our security controls, data privacy practices, and backup policies meet the highest enterprise standards. Enterprise Plan customers can request a copy of our compliance reports by opening a Support Ticket signed by an Administrator. We continuously monitor our infrastructure for vulnerabilities and enforce strict IP restrictions across our internal networks. These measures ensure your workspace and API Keys remain secure.', false),
('Managing Data Residency and Backup Policy', 'We offer data residency options for Enterprise Plan customers, allowing you to specify whether your data is stored in United States or European Union data centers. This ensures compliance with regional data privacy laws like GDPR. All data is backed up daily, with backups retained for thirty days in geographically distinct locations. In the event of a disaster, our recovery point objective (RPO) is one hour, and our recovery time objective (RTO) is four hours. You can request a Data Export at any time to verify your information is intact.', false),
('Utilizing the Sandbox Environment', 'The Developer Portal provides access to a dedicated sandbox environment for testing API integrations without affecting live production data. You can generate test API Keys prefixed with test_ to authenticate requests against this isolated environment. Webhook endpoints can also be configured to trigger from sandbox events, allowing you to test signature validation safely. No billing charges are incurred in the sandbox, and all data is reset every twenty-four hours. This environment is essential for validating retry strategies and timeout handling before deployment.', false),
('Managing Feature Flags and System Announcements', 'Administrators can control the rollout of new functionality using feature flags located in the Organization Settings. This allows you to enable beta features for a specific internal team before deploying them to the entire workspace. When a feature flag is toggled, a system announcement is automatically posted to the dashboard to alert users of the change. If a feature causes application crash issues, Administrators can instantly disable the flag to revert to the previous stable state. This granular control ensures smooth transitions during platform updates.', false),
('Handling User Suspension and License Management', 'If a user violates your internal security policies, an Administrator can temporarily suspend their access account. A suspended user cannot sign in or consume API Quotas, but their data remains intact. To permanently free up a seat for a new employee, you must fully deactivate the suspended user in the Organization Settings. License management automatically adjusts your subscription billing based on the number of active, non-suspended users. Ensure you monitor your active license count to avoid unexpected payment failures during your renewal cycle.', false);